### Loess Model

```{r}
df = insurance
df$smoker = ifelse(df$smoker=="yes",1,0)
df$sex = as.numeric(df$sex)
df$ne = ifelse(df$region=="northeast",1,0)
df$nw = ifelse(df$region=="northwest",1,0)
df$se = ifelse(df$region=="southeast",1,0)
df$sw = ifelse(df$region=="southwest",1,0)
fit_loess = loess(log~age*bmi*smoker * sex,data=df,degree = 1,span=0.4)
#fit_loess = loess(log~age*bmi*smoker + sex,data=df,degree = 1,span=0.4)
summary(fit_loess)
```


```{r}
insurance1.loess.df = data.frame(insurance, .fitted = fitted.values(fit_loess), .resid = residuals(fit_loess))

```

```{r}
print(var(fitted.values(fit_loess))/(var(fitted.values(fit_loess)) + var(residuals(fit_loess))))

```

### Fitted v/s Residuals Plot

```{r}
ggplot(insurance1.loess.df,aes(y=.resid,x=.fitted)) + geom_point()+ geom_smooth(method="loess")+geom_abline(slope = 0, intercept = 0) + labs(title = "Fitted vs Residuals", x = "Fitted values", y = "Residual values")
```

### Age v/s Fitted Values Facetted by BMI Categories and colored by Gender and Smoking habit

```{r}
